# BoxScan Monorepo — Environment Variable Reference
#
# This file documents how mobile and backend variables relate to each other.
# It is NOT loaded by any service — each service has its own .env file.
#
# HOW TO SET UP:
#   1. Copy backend/.env.example  ->  backend/.env   and fill in real values
#   2. Copy mobile/.env.example   ->  mobile/.env.local  and fill in real values
#   3. The two critical values that MUST match are marked with <-- SYNC below.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  BACKEND (backend/.env)              MOBILE (mobile/.env.local)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Server address — mobile must point to this, using the network-accessible IP
# (not "localhost", which resolves to the device itself on mobile).
#
#   backend/.env          APP_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.x:3000
#   mobile/.env.local     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.x:3000   <-- SYNC (same IP/port)

# Shared secret — must be identical in both files.
# Generate once:  openssl rand -hex 32
#
#   backend/.env          API_SHARED_SECRET=<strong-random-secret>
#   mobile/.env.local     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_KEY=<strong-random-secret>          <-- SYNC (same value)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  BACKEND-ONLY VARIABLES  (no mobile equivalent)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PORT=3000
# STORAGE_PROVIDER=local
# UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
# AI_PROVIDER=mock                   # mock | gemini | local
# GEMINI_API_KEY=CHANGE_ME
# AI_GATEWAY_URL=
# MAX_UPLOAD_MB=10
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8081,http://localhost:19006
